  "body": "As a follow-up to #7813, we want to ensure we enforce some strong invariants recommended by EIP-3076 after slashing protection data is imported into the validator client. Given this is high risk to include in a minor semver patch, we need to test it for a while and will be separate from #7813, which is safe to go in a minor patch release.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Support the invariant below:\r\n> Refuse to sign any block with slot <= min(b.slot for b in data.signed_blocks if b.pubkey == proposer_pubkey), except if it is a repeat signing as determined by the signing_root.\r\n- [ ]  Support the invariant below #7966\r\n> Refuse to sign any attestation with source epoch less than the minimum source epoch present in that signerâ€™s attestations (as seen in data.signed_attestations)\r\n- [ ] Allow resubmission of blocks with the same signing root in slashing protection #7866\r\n\r\nIf there is a problem with the code above, we can prevent all prysm validators from attesting or proposing, so great care must be taken with this feature.\r\n",
